“The Mudhaliyar—he erred in his choice. As he so often did, [blinded by sentiment where there should have been strategy.] His mistake must not become the South’s. She must be stripped of her claim before the rot spreads through the court.”
He gestured vaguely toward the ancestral crests looming above them.
[“This room was not built for charity, sister. It was built for rule. ]For legacy. And you know as well as I do — her name does not belong in stone.”
